<task id="042" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4">
  <metadata>
    <title>W-4 (FR-02): Wire Assistant → Workspace mount source — first end-to-end widget_load demo (recommended: PDF upload → DocumentViewer tab)</title>
    <phase>4: Workspace builder + mount-source wiring</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>8</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>010, 040</dependencies>
    <blocks>none</blocks>
    <tags>frontend, react, fluent-ui, e2e-test, deploy</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies `.ts/.tsx` source; tags include `frontend`/`react`/`fluent-ui`; 10+ steps; depends on 010 (W-1 model) and 040 (wizard fix); applies multiple load-bearing ADRs (021, 022, 025, 028). FULL rigor — Step 9.5 quality gates mandatory.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>depends on 010 (W-1 model) and 040 (wizard catalog fix)</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Wire the Assistant pane to dispatch `widget_load` on the `PaneEventBus.workspace`
    channel, mounting a widget as a new workspace tab. At task start the operator selects
    the demo scenario (per OC-R4-07); the recommended scenario is "user uploads PDF in chat
    → DocumentViewer widget mounts as a workspace tab". Implement the Assistant-side
    dispatcher; wire/build the receiving widget into `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry` if not
    already registered; demonstrate the demo end-to-end on the dev environment. Use typed
    PaneEventBus channels (ADR-025 — no `any` payloads) and `authenticatedFetch` for any
    BFF calls (ADR-028).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer expert in PaneEventBus (`@spaarke/ai-widgets`),
    `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry`, Assistant pane internals (`src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/
    components/conversation/`), React 19 + Fluent UI v9, and ADR-028 function-based auth.
    Bias toward the smallest end-to-end demo that proves the pattern — defer broad coverage
    to a follow-up. Per plan.original.md §8 Risk R-7: if scope risks exceeding 8h, ship the
    dispatch + ONE viewer widget and defer broader coverage.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Operator-visible end-to-end demo on the dev environment: a user action in the Assistant
    pane (recommended: PDF upload in chat) dispatches `widget_load` on the workspace
    channel; the receiving widget mounts as a new tab in the Workspace pane; the tab is
    selectable; the tab is closable per existing tab semantics. Code changes meet ADR-021
    (Fluent v9 tokens), ADR-022 (React 19), ADR-025 (typed PaneEventBus channels — no
    `any`), and ADR-028 (function-based auth — no token snapshots). FR-02 acceptance
    criteria satisfied. Build + deploy green; UI tests pass including dark-mode.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per plan §4 Phase 4 and FR-02, the Assistant pane is one of two not-yet-implemented
      mount sources for the Workspace pane (the other is Context, addressed by W-5 / task
      043). Today the workspace mounts content via the user picker + workspace dropdown
      only. R4's first end-to-end `widget_load` dispatch lands here. The receiving wrapper
      is `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry` (Direct widget wrapper per the two-wrapper model from
      W-1) — NOT `LegalWorkspaceApp` (Dashboard wrapper). The PaneEventBus pattern is
      codified in ADR-025 (created by task 012, which is also a Phase 1 dep — task 010
      depends on the dashboard+widget model doc which references ADR-025). The R3 Calendar
      widget Pattern D (task 115) is the canonical worked example for a shared-lib widget
      mounted via the registry — a useful reference for the receiving widget.

      Per OC-R4-07 (2026-05-25): "Operator chooses at task time; recommended: PDF upload in
      chat → DocumentViewer tab". This means: (a) the dispatcher in the Assistant pane
      observes a user upload action; (b) it constructs a typed `widget_load` payload
      identifying the widget type (e.g., `document-viewer`) and the data (file reference,
      blob ID, etc.); (c) it dispatches on the workspace channel; (d) the workspace pane's
      mount logic (existing, from R3) handles the event and resolves the widget from
      `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry`; (e) the widget renders as a new tab.

      Decision points the operator may surface at task start: (1) which exact upload type
      to wire (PDF only, or any file?), (2) does the existing DocumentViewer widget meet
      the demo bar, or does this task ship a minimal stub viewer? Stay scoped per Risk R-7.

      ADR-028 invariants: NO token snapshots in props/state. Use `useAuth()` +
      `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth` for any BFF call inside the widget. ADR-025
      invariant: PaneEventBus channels are typed — `widget_load` payload type must be
      declared in `PaneEventTypes.ts` (extend if needed; don't widen to `any`).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/ConversationPane.tsx</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventBus.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventBusContext.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventTypes.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/useDispatchPaneEvent.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/registry/WorkspaceWidgetRegistry.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/ (existing widgets — DocumentViewer or similar)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 tokens only. NO hex, NO `rgba()`, NO Fluent v8.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 only for Code Pages. NO React 16 fallbacks.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-025">PaneEventBus channels MUST be typed — NO `any` payloads. Extend `PaneEventTypes.ts` for the `widget_load` payload shape (widget type ID + data) and reuse for both W-4 and W-5.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Function-based auth via `@spaarke/auth` `authenticatedFetch`. NO token snapshots in props/state. NO new auth mechanisms.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Shared widgets live in `@spaarke/ai-widgets` (or `@spaarke/*` lib family). Don't duplicate widget code inside SpaarkeAi solution.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Scope guard per Risk R-7: ship dispatch + ONE viewer widget end-to-end. Broader widget coverage is OUT OF SCOPE for this task — defer to follow-up.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Operator confirms demo scenario at task start (OC-R4-07). Record the chosen scenario in &lt;notes&gt;.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">If a NEW widget is created for the demo, it MUST register via `registerWorkspaceWidget()` in a clean module-load registration file, not inline in the Assistant pane.</constraint>
  </constraints>

