  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Confirm dependencies">
      Verify tasks 010 (W-1 dashboard+widget model doc) and 040 (wizard catalog fix) are ✅ in TASK-INDEX.md. If either is not complete, STOP and surface the blocker per CLAUDE.md "Human Escalation Triggers".
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Operator confirms demo scenario">
      Surface OC-R4-07 to operator: confirm recommended "PDF upload in chat → DocumentViewer tab" OR substitute scenario. Record the choice in &lt;notes&gt; at task end. Without the operator's choice, do NOT proceed past Step 3.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Load context">
      Read W-1 doc (010 output), ADR-025, ADR-028, PaneEventBus source files, ConversationPane source, WorkspaceWidgetRegistry source, and Calendar widget Pattern D reference.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Design dispatch payload">
      Define / extend the typed payload for `widget_load` on the workspace channel in `PaneEventTypes.ts`. Required fields: widget type ID (string union from registered types), title (string), data (typed per widget). NO `any` per ADR-025. Add JSDoc.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Choose / build receiving widget">
      If an existing DocumentViewer widget in `@spaarke/ai-widgets` meets the demo bar, use it (verify it's already registered via `registerWorkspaceWidget()`). If not, build a minimal widget in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/` + register it via a dedicated registration file. Follow Calendar Pattern D shape. Use `useAuth()` + `authenticatedFetch` for any BFF call inside the widget (ADR-028).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Implement dispatcher in Assistant pane">
      Add the dispatch logic in `ConversationPane.tsx` (or a dedicated hook in the conversation/ folder). Trigger: the chosen user action (per Step 2 — recommended: PDF upload finished + file is a PDF). Construct the typed payload + call `useDispatchPaneEvent()` with channel `workspace` and event `widget_load`. Keep dispatcher logic small, testable, and isolated.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify Workspace pane receives + mounts">
      Confirm the existing Workspace pane mount logic (from R3) subscribes to the workspace channel and handles `widget_load` by resolving the widget via `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry` and rendering as a new tab. If a gap is discovered, fix in place — DO NOT introduce new channel mechanics.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Build">
      Run `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund` (if needed) and `npm run build` for SpaarkeAi solution AND `@spaarke/ai-widgets` shared lib. Verify both succeed with 0 errors. Run `tsc --noEmit` on touched packages.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Unit tests">
      Add focused tests: (a) dispatcher constructs the correct typed payload for the chosen scenario; (b) Workspace pane subscribes to `widget_load` and calls `resolveWorkspaceWidget()` with the right ID. Mock PaneEventBus / `useDispatchPaneEvent` per existing test patterns.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Deploy">
      Deploy SpaarkeAi via `code-page-deploy` skill. Verify deployment to dev environment succeeds.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="UI test">
      Per &lt;ui-tests&gt; below: execute the end-to-end demo on the dev environment; verify tab appears, is selectable, is closable; verify dark-mode parity. Capture screenshots / browser console clean.
    </step>
    <step order="12" name="Bundle-size check">
      Measure SpaarkeAi gzip bundle delta (NFR-08 budget: ≤+50 KB vs 918 KB R3 baseline). Record in &lt;notes&gt;. If a new widget was added, lazy-load via registry factory to keep delta near zero.
    </step>
    <step order="13" name="Update TASK-INDEX">
      Edit `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: flip task 042 from 🔲 → ✅ completed.
    </step>
    <step order="14" name="Document deviations + operator demo">
      Record the chosen demo scenario, any pivots, and the bundle-size delta in `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/`. Surface the live demo to the operator for FR-02 acceptance sign-off.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="npm">Build + tests for SpaarkeAi solution and @spaarke/ai-widgets shared lib</tool>
    <tool name="terminal">Shell commands for build / install / git status / tsc --noEmit</tool>
    <tool name="Skill">code-page-deploy for SpaarkeAi web resource deployment; ui-test for browser-based verification</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/ConversationPane.tsx (or dedicated hook)</output>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/events/PaneEventTypes.ts (extended)</output>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/ (new or extended widget)</output>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/registry/ (registration file if new widget)</output>
