    <output type="test">src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/__tests__/ (registry/payload tests)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (status flip)</output>
  </outputs>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Assistant → Workspace end-to-end demo (FR-02 acceptance)">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?appid={app-id}&amp;pagetype=custom&amp;name=sprk_spaarkeai</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Open SpaarkeAi in the dev environment; verify Assistant + Workspace + Context panes are visible</step>
        <step>Perform the chosen demo trigger (e.g., upload a PDF in the chat input)</step>
        <step>Observe the Workspace pane mount a new tab labeled with the widget title (e.g., file name)</step>
        <step>Verify the new tab is selectable (click and observe activation)</step>
        <step>Verify the widget renders content correctly (e.g., DocumentViewer shows the PDF / file preview)</step>
        <step>Verify the tab is closable (close button works; tab disappears; existing tabs unaffected)</step>
        <step>Check browser console: 0 JavaScript errors</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>End-to-end demo works as described in FR-02 acceptance; no console errors; tab semantics preserved.</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="Dark Mode Compliance (ADR-021)">
      <steps>
        <step>Toggle dark mode in D365 settings</step>
        <step>Repeat the demo trigger</step>
        <step>Verify the new tab and its widget render correctly in dark mode (no white-on-white, no black-on-black)</step>
        <step>Verify all colors use Fluent v9 semantic tokens (inspect Computed styles for `var(--colorNeutral*)` etc.)</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Dark-mode renders cleanly; all colors via Fluent v9 semantic tokens per ADR-021.</expected>
    </test>

    <test name="PaneEventBus type safety (ADR-025)">
      <steps>
        <step>Inspect the dispatched event in browser devtools (PaneEventBus instrumentation or React DevTools)</step>
        <step>Verify the payload shape matches the declared TypeScript type for `widget_load`</step>
        <step>Confirm no `any` casts in the dispatch path (review code in the task PR)</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Payload is typed end-to-end; no `any` casts.</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the operator triggers the chosen demo action in the Assistant pane, When the action completes, Then a `widget_load` event is dispatched on the workspace channel with a typed payload identifying the widget + data.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the workspace channel receives a `widget_load` event, When the Workspace pane handles it, Then the widget resolves via `WorkspaceWidgetRegistry` and mounts as a new tab.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the new tab is mounted, When the user clicks the tab, Then it becomes active; When the user closes it, Then it is removed without affecting other tabs.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given ADR-025 requires typed channels, When the code is reviewed, Then no `any` payload types appear in the dispatch path; `widget_load` payload is declared in `PaneEventTypes.ts`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given ADR-028 requires function-based auth, When the receiving widget calls the BFF, Then it uses `authenticatedFetch` from `@spaarke/auth`; NO token snapshots in props/state.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given ADR-021 requires Fluent v9 tokens, When the new tab renders in light + dark mode, Then all colors use semantic tokens; no hardcoded hex/rgba.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the SpaarkeAi bundle has a 918 KB R3 baseline (NFR-08), When this task's deploy completes, Then bundle delta is ≤+50 KB or justified in notes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given task 042 is executing, When this task completes, Then TASK-INDEX.md shows task 042 as ✅ completed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Operator MUST confirm the demo scenario at task start per OC-R4-07. Recommended: "user uploads PDF in chat → DocumentViewer widget mounts as workspace tab". Alternative scenarios include "assistant suggests opening a document → workspace tab with viewer", or "assistant returns a search result → workspace tab with result viewer". Record the operator's choice in this notes block at task close.

    Per Risk R-7 in plan.original.md §8: if scope risks blowing the 8h estimate, ship dispatch + ONE viewer widget end-to-end and defer broader coverage to a follow-up. DO NOT widen the demo at the cost of incomplete delivery.

    The Calendar widget Pattern D (R3 task 115) is the canonical reference for the receiving widget's shape. If a new widget is built (e.g., a minimal DocumentViewer), follow that pattern: shared-lib component + thin registration shim. DO NOT inline widget code in the Assistant pane.

    `PaneEventTypes.ts` extension: the `widget_load` event type SHOULD be reusable for W-5 (task 043) — design the payload to accommodate both Assistant-initiated and Context-initiated dispatches. Task 043 will consume the same type.

    This task BLOCKS nothing in Phase 4 (043 depends on 010, not on 042). Therefore 042 + 043 can run in parallel (parallel-group E) — they touch different code paths (Assistant pane vs Context wizard) but both depend on 010 (W-1 model).

    AUTO-DEMOTION: this task does NOT touch `.claude/` paths, so the `.claude/` permission boundary does not apply. The `parallel-safe=false` here is because of hard task-dependency (010 + 040), not file-overlap.
  </notes>

